definition: used before countable or singular nouns referring to people or things that have not already been mentioned
making you feel that you can understand and have sympathy with somebody/something
to go back into a previous condition or into a worse state after making an improvement
to give a lot of your time and effort to a particular activity or purpose because you think it is important
to think or say that someone or something is responsible for something bad
[countable] a structure such as a house, school, or factory that has a roof and walls
a room or building used for scientific research, experiments, testing, etc.
the system of communication in speech and writing that is used by people of a particular country or area
willing to understand and respect other people's behavior, opinions, etc., especially when they are different from your own; believing people should be able to choose how they behave
